{
  "book": 18,
  "chapter": 32,
  "sections": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "heading": "以利戶的話"
    },
    {
      "type": "ref-heading",
      "heading": "（32‧1－37‧24）"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 1,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Then these three men ceased answering Job, because he was righteous in his own eyes. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 2,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "But the anger of Elihu the son of Barachel the Buzite, of the family of Ram burned; against Job his anger burned because he justified himself before God. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 3,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "And his anger burned against his three friends because they had found no answer, and yet had condemned Job. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 4,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Now Elihu had waited to speak to Job because they were years older than he. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 5,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "And when Elihu saw that there was no answer in the mouth of the three men his anger burned. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 5,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 6,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "So Elihu the son of Barachel the Buzite spoke out and said, “I am young in years and you are old; Therefore I was shy and afraid to tell you what I think. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 6,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "So Elihu the son of Barachel the Buzite spoke out and said, “I am young in years and you are old; Therefore I was shy and afraid to tell you what I think."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 6,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "So Elihu the son of Barachel the Buzite spoke out and said, “I am young in years and you are old; Therefore I was shy and afraid to tell you what I think."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 6,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 7,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "I thought age should speak, And increased years should teach wisdom. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 7,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "I thought age should speak, And increased years should teach wisdom."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 7,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 8,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "But it is a spirit in man, And the breath of the Almighty gives them understanding. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 8,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "But it is a spirit in man, And the breath of the Almighty gives them understanding."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 8,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 9,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "The abundant in years may not be wise, Nor may elders understand justice. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 9,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "The abundant in years may not be wise, Nor may elders understand justice."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 9,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 10,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "So I say, ‘Listen to me, I too will tell what I think.’ "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 10,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "So I say, ‘Listen to me, I too will tell what I think.’"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 10,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 11,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "“Behold, I waited for your words, I listened to your reasonings, While you pondered what to say. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 11,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "“Behold, I waited for your words, I listened to your reasonings, While you pondered what to say."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 11,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "“Behold, I waited for your words, I listened to your reasonings, While you pondered what to say."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 11,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 12,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "I even paid close attention to you; Indeed, there was no one who refuted Job, Not one of you who answered his words. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 12,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "I even paid close attention to you; Indeed, there was no one who refuted Job, Not one of you who answered his words."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 12,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "I even paid close attention to you; Indeed, there was no one who refuted Job, Not one of you who answered his words."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 12,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 13,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Do not say, ‘We have found wisdom; God will rout him, not man.’ "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 13,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "Do not say, ‘We have found wisdom; God will rout him, not man.’"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 13,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 14,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "For he has not arranged his words against me, Nor will I reply to him with your arguments. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 14,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "For he has not arranged his words against me, Nor will I reply to him with your arguments."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 14,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 15,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "“They are dismayed, they no longer answer; Words have failed them. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 15,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "“They are dismayed, they no longer answer; Words have failed them."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 15,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 16,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Shall I wait, because they do not speak, Because they stop and no longer answer? "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 16,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "Shall I wait, because they do not speak, Because they stop and no longer answer?"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 16,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 17,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "I too will answer my share, I also will tell my opinion. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 17,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "I too will answer my share, I also will tell my opinion."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 17,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 18,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "For I am full of words; The spirit within me constrains me. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 18,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "For I am full of words; The spirit within me constrains me."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 18,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 19,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Behold, my belly is like unvented wine, Like new wineskins it is about to burst. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 19,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "Behold, my belly is like unvented wine, Like new wineskins it is about to burst."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 19,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 20,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Let me speak that I may get relief; Let me open my lips and answer. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 20,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "Let me speak that I may get relief; Let me open my lips and answer."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 20,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 21,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Let me now be partial to no one, Nor flatter any man. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 21,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "Let me now be partial to no one, Nor flatter any man."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 21,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 22,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "For I do not know how to flatter, Else my Maker would soon take me away. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 22,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "For I do not know how to flatter, Else my Maker would soon take me away."
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
